text: Iera Echebarría Fernández (born 20 October 1992) is a Spanish rugby sevens player. She competed for Spain at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Brazil. She was a member of the Spanish women's sevens squad. She was part of the squad that secured the final Olympic spot for the Rio Olympics. == References == == External links == * * Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:Spain international women's rugby union players Category:Spain international women's rugby sevens players Category:Olympic rugby sevens players of Spain Category:Rugby sevens players at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
